# Git Workflow

- Work in small, reviewable increments; avoid giant mixed-purpose changes.
- Keep one logical change per commit.
- Write commit messages that explain intent and impact, not only file edits.
- Do not commit secrets, tokens, or environment files with sensitive values.
- Before finalizing changes, check for accidental debug code and noisy logs.

# Branch and PR Hygiene

- Use descriptive branch names tied to feature/fix intent.
- Keep pull requests focused to one main outcome.
- Include a short test plan for each PR (what was verified and how).
- Call out risks, migrations, or data-impacting changes explicitly.

# Safety

- Avoid destructive git actions unless explicitly requested by project owner.
- Preserve unrelated local changes; do not revert work outside current scope.
